	- **INTRODUCTION**

       

         Ships, offshore platforms, petroleum storage tanks, and sea-crossing bridges are important structures to industry and economy. In order to keep them working for longer time, it is very necessary to conduct regular surface maintenances to those high structures at some intervals, including non-destructive testing, removal of rust, and stripping of corrosion. But this is a very difficult task to be done manually – firstly, due to limited maneuverability. Secondly, the risk of falling from scaff-holdings and thirdly it adds to additional costs and time.

         

         Technologies of wall-climbing robots have been researched for a few decades. Considering the high working surfaces, adhesion-locomotion system plays an important role in a wall-climbing robot. It provides an adhesive force to produce enough friction for sustaining the weight of robot and payloads. It provides a climbing movement on the surface with high velocity and maneuverability.

	         Some of the applications of adhesion – locomotive system are:

- Weld Inspection

- Hull Inspection

- Inspection of Wind Turbines

- Coating

- Tanker cleaning

- **P****ROJECT DESCRIPTION**

