- ** ****MANUFACTURING**

For manufacturing of the wheel prototype three options were considered:- 

- Conventional machining

- Water Jet

- 3D Printing

There were few issues that came up with the first two methods of machining. For the conventional machining the appropriate size of the drilling and milling tool was not available. Thus due to limited space in the cutout the motion of the tool was restricted and the required cutout was not possible.

For the water jet cutting method the problem of fine edges and tool unavailability was solved, but the manufacturing cost of the water jet cutting was out of the budget of project. Finally the option of 3D Printing was chosen for manufacturing the wheel which eliminated all the challenges in manufacturing.

Another issue during the manufacturing of the magnetic wheel was the unavailability of required size and the grade of the magnet. The issue of size of magnet was tackled by scaling the dimensions of the wheel according to the available size in a way that didn’t affect the basic principle and effectiveness of the design.

- **MAGNETIC WHEEL CATALOGUE**

Based on the research, calculations, and design a catalogue was generated which provided variety of different magnetic wheels with different payload capacity.

It consists majorly of two parts:- 

- Wheel dimensions

- Weight sustained

The dimensional part consists of the 

- Width of the wheel

- Diameter of the wheel

- Edge length of the square face of the magnet

- Inner diameter and outer diameter which defines the position of Halbach array from center of the circle.

By defining the above dimensions, the maximum weight sustained by the wheel can be obtained. Based on the above dimensions two catalogues were prepared – Catalogue 1 and Catalogue 2.

- **Catalogue 1**

The categorization of different magnetic wheels in this catalogue is done on the basis of the easy availability of the magnets. The size of the magnet is the independent variable in this catalogue and the dependent variables are the various dimensions of the wheel and the output is the maximum weight sustained by the wheel.

- **Catalogue 2**

The categorization of different magnetic wheels in this catalogue does not focus on the easy availability of the magnets. Rather it provides variety of load capacities as per the requirement of the user. This catalogue provides with weight carrying capacity ranging from 5 kg to 110 kg with slabs of 5 kgs.

